		<h1 style="text-align:center">SERVICES AGREEMENT</h1>
		<p>
			This Services Agreement ("Agreement") is entered into the <?=date('jS',strtotime($date))?> day of <?=date('F',strtotime($date))?>, <?=date('Y',strtotime($date))?> (the "Effective Date"), by and between Lobos Interstate Services, LLC, a Utah limited liability company ( "Lobos"), and
			<?=$fullname?>, personally ("Driver") (also referred to as "Client")
		</p>
		<p>
			WHEREAS, Lobos assists individual truck drivers in forming, purchasing, and selling business entities, obtaining necessary licenses and permits to operate as an owner operator and/or motor carrier, provides transportation consulting, and provides safety compliance consulting to the drivers, owner operators and motor carriers;
		</p>
		<p>
			WHEREAS, Lobos also offers financing to individual truck drivers to pay for acquisition, start-up,	formation, and selling costs, licensing and permitting fees, and safety and compliance costs;
		</p>
		<p>
			WHEREAS, Lobos also offers financing to individual truck drivers to pay for acquisition, start-up,	formation, and selling costs, licensing and permitting fees, and safety and compliance costs;
		</p>
		<p>
			WHEREAS, the Driver desires to obtain ownership interest in the motor carrier or trucking company ("Company") that the Driver participates in, or that Lobos anticipates that the Driver will participate in (Participation is indicated by the Driver entering in, or operating of, one or more of the Company's leased, owned, or	rented motor vehicles);
		</p>
		<p>
			WHEREAS, the Driver desires to form a new company in the event that the opportunity to obtain ownership interest in a pre-existing motor carrier or trucking company is not available;
		</p>
		<p>
			WHEREAS, if the Company does not possess a motor carrier authority, the Driver desires that the	Company acquire a motor carrier authority as the opportunity arises;
		</p>
		<p>
			WHEREAS, the Driver desires to relinquish ownership interest in the trucking companies the Driver is not participating in;
		</p>
		<p>
			WHEREAS, the Driver desires to engage Lobos to provide the services and financing in connection with the Driver's formation, purchasing, selling, and operation of the Company, and Lobos is willing to provide said	Services and Financing on the terms and conditions set forth herein;
		</p>
		<p>
			NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing recitals which are deemed contractual, the covenants and promises contained herein, and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of	which are hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereto, each intending to be legally bound hereby, agree as follows:
		</p>
		<ol>
			<li>Services Provided by Lobos. Lobos agrees to pay for and provide the following services for and in behalf of the Client (the "Services"):
				<ol type="a">
					<li>Purchasing, Selling, and Registration of Company. Lobos shall do the following:
						<ol type="i">
							<li>Manage or conduct the transactions in which the Client (1) obtains ownership interest in	the Company, (2) relinquishes ownership interest in the Company. The Client desires to obtain ownership interest in every trucking company that the Client participates in. The Client desires to relinquish ownership interest in any trucking company that the Client no longer participates in. Participation is indicated by the Driver entering in or operating one or more of the Company's leased, owned, or rented motor vehicles. Lobos shall manage these transactions by representing the client as an authorized representative, creating, signing, filing, and submitting all required paperwork and documents necessary to perfect these transactions. These documents include but are not	limited to the following: Updated Certificate of Organization and other corporate docs needed to be filed with the state; 8822-B form submitted to the Department of the Treasury Internal Revenue Service; Updated OP-1 and MCS-150 to be filed with the appropriate government agencies; And all necessary contracts such as partnership agreements, buy/sell agreements, and any other documents deemed necessary by Lobos to properly manage these transactions. In the situation where the opportunity to obtain ownership interest in an existing entity does not exist, Lobos shall assist the Client in the formation of a new trucking company and/or motor carrier by doing the following:
								<ol type="1">
									<li>Filing the Certificate of Organization and Statement of Authority to register the Company with the Utah State Corporate Division or similar documentation any other state may require as deemed necessary by Lobos.</li>
									<li>Obtaining a federal employment identification number from the Internal Revenue Service for the Company. This contract constitutes authority granted by the Driver and Company to Lobos' employees to sign the IRS Form SS-4 and other Federal and State documents as an authorized representative.</li>
									<li>Obtaining physical and mailing addresses (such as a post office box, UPS mail box, and/or virtual office spaces) for and in behalf of the Company.</li>
								</ol>
							</li>
							<li>
								Retrieve, open, and hold mail for and on behalf of the Company and Driver that is received as such post office boxes or addresses. Lobos shall within one (1) business day notify the Company of any mail that Lobos deems to be time sensitive. Lobos shall hold the other pieces of mail for pick up by the Company. If it is determined that the mail will not be picked up by Driver, Lobos shall mark the mail Return to Sender.
							</li>
							<li>
								Create and obtain a company profile for the new entity including a phone number, fax number, principal place of business and mailing address.
							</li>
							<li>
								Serve as Company's registered agent with the State or assign a 3rd party company to be	the registered agent with the State. The Company authorizes Lobos or the assigned 3rd party to perform any and all services required as a registered agent, including but not limited to preparing and filing an annual report with the Secretary of State and receiving service of process on behalf of the Company. The Company authorizes Lobos or	the assigned 3rd party to take all such actions and steps that may be required as registered agent.
							</li>
							<li>
								Make any updates or required changes to the registration with the State of Utah or other state in which the Company is registered to do business.
							</li>
						</ol>
					</li>
					<li>
						Transportation Consulting Services. Lobos shall provide over-the-phone trainings to the Company and its Driver regarding profit maximization and efficiency in the industry at the reasonable request of the Company. Lobos shall also provide over-the-phone reviews of the Company profit and loss statements at the request of the Company.
					</li>
					<li>
						Coordination of Leasing On to Motor Carrier. In the event that the Company is considered does not have motor carrier authority, Lobos shall exercise its reasonable best efforts to coordinate with motor carriers to assist the Company in finding and contracting with a motor carrier to lease on to their authority with the ability to operate in interstate commerce. The Company and Driver hereby grant and give the authority to Lobos to enter into such lease agreements for and in behalf of the Company and Driver so long as: the lease rate is no less than $1.30 per mile; the term of such lease is for no more than one (1) year; and other standard and customary terms of the industry are set forth in the lease agreement.
					</li>
					<li>
						Application for USDOT, FMCSA, and Other Licenses, Permits, and Authorities. In the event that the Company has the opportunity to become a motor carrier, Lobos, or a 3rd party engaged by Lobos, shall apply for the following licenses and permits on behalf of the Company:
						<ol type="i">
							<li>USDOT number and authority with the USDOT;</li>
							<li>Operating Authority (MC number) with FMCSA;</li>
							<li>All operating licenses and permits on behalf of the Company required for the Company to legally operate in interstate commerce, including various state permits in which the Company will operate.</li>
						</ol>
					</li>
					<li>
						Compliance Consulting and Management. In the event that the Company becomes a motor carrier, Lobos shall provide the following services:
						<ol type="i">
							<li>Enroll drivers in drug consortium;</li>
							<li>Maintain driver qualification files;</li>
							<li>Review driver log books;</li>
							<li>Update MCS-150;</li>
							<li>Update OP-1 Form;</li>
							<li>Update the Company's profile maintained by FMCSA, USDOT and any other entities that require periodic maintenance of business profiles. Notwithstanding the foregoing, while Lobos as the authority to update the Company's profile, it is the ultimate responsibility and liability of the Company to maintain updated profiles. Lobos can only update and maintain profiles as correct information is provided to Lobos;</li>
							<li>Represent Company as a safety manager in any compliance related matter, including during a safety audit;</li>
							<p>Lobos will not coordinate or handle pre-employment drug testing on behalf of the Company. The Company shall be responsible to receive pre-employment drug tests directly from potential drivers. Lobos may assist individual drivers in obtaining pre-employment drug tests, but such results are confidential between the individual drivers and Lobos and may not be shared with the Company.</p>
						</ol>
					</li>
					<li>
						Grant of Authority and Permission to Lobos. The Company and Driver hereby explicitly grants to Lobos, its officers, managers, employees and designated agents the full authority and permission necessary to perform the services listed in Section 1 above, in the broadest sense allowable under law. Further permissions and authorities granted by the Company and Driver to Lobos regarding Lobos representations as a safety manager for the Company and Driver is set forth in Power of Attorney for Safety Manager which is attached hereto as Exhibit "A" and incorporated herein by this reference.
					</li>
				</ol>
			</li>
			<li>
				Compensation for Services. For the Services provided in Sections 1(a), (b), (c), (d) and (e) the Company hereby agrees to pay to Lobos the greater of $60.00 per week or $0.04 per odometer mile for the Driver's truck for such week. Such payments, as applicable, shall be remitted to Lobos weekly on Tuesday of the subsequent week based on previous week's mileage, as applicable. It is understood that Lobos may receive payment from a limited cooperative association of which the Company is a member.
			</li>
			<li>
				Term. This Agreement shall continue for a period of eight (8) weeks from the Effective Date. This Agreement shall automatically renew for a period of eight (8) weeks if neither party provides at least fourteen (14) days written notice to the other party prior to the end of the term. Notwithstanding the foregoing, either party may terminate this Agreement at any time by giving the other party fourteen (14) days written notice; provided however that if the Driver terminates this Agreement based on such notice, it shall pay Lobos the Termination Fee set forth below in Section 5(b).
			</li>
			<li>
				Security for Obligations; Creation of Security Interest.
				<ol type="a">
					<li>Grant of Security Interest by Driver. In consideration for payment of costs for the Services and for the Services themselves and of the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement, the Driver hereby grants to Lobos a security interest in and to all of his membership and ownership interests in and to the Company and all proceeds of the foregoing (including, without limitation, insurance proceeds) and substitutions therefore held or controlled by the Driver (the "Driver's Collateral"). The Driver hereby authorizes the Lobos to take whatever steps necessary to perfect its interests in the Driver's Collateral, including the filing of a UCC1 - Financing Statement.</li>
					<li>Grant of Security Interest by Company. In consideration for payment of costs for the Services and for the Services themselves and of the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement, the Company hereby grants to Lobos a security interest in all its inventory, equipment, vehicles and all personal property, tangible and intangible, whether presently existing or hereafter created or acquired, including, without limitation, all accounts, chattel paper, documents, instruments, money, deposit accounts, accounts receivable, general intangibles and all proceeds of the foregoing (including, without limitation, insurance proceeds) and substitutions therefore held or controlled by Debtor (the "Company Collateral"). The Company hereby authorizes Lobos to take whatever steps necessary to perfect its interests in the Company's Collateral, including the filing of a UCC1 - Financing Statement. And being listed as a lien holder on the appropriate Certificate of Title for any vehicles.</li>
					<li>Obligations Secured. The security interest created above is to secure the obligations of the Driver and Company as set forth in this Agreement.</li>
				</ol>
			</li>
