							<li>Ceasing to participate, by the Driver, in any Company as a client of Lobos during the term of the Agreement;</li>
							<li>A filing of any petition under the United States Bankruptcy Act or any similar state proceeding or filing made by any other person against the Company or the Driver of any petition under the United States Bankruptcy Act or any similar state proceeding which is not cured, dismissed or stayed within 60 days, or the application for, or appointment of, a receiver of the Company or Driver's property; appointment of a committee of the Company or the Driver's creditors, or the making by the Company or the Driver an assignment for benefit of creditors</li>
							<li>If any representation or warranty or any other statement of fact herein or in any writing, certificate, report, or statement at any time furnished to Lobos pursuant to or in connection with this Agreement, or otherwise, shall be false or misleading in any material respect;</li>
						</ol>
					</li>
					<li>Remedies. The Driver and Company have five (5) days from written notice of the occurrence of an Event of Default to pay a termination fee of $10,000 ("Termination Fee"). Driver and Company further acknowledges that the sums to be paid pursuant to this Section (i) constitute agreed upon and liquidated damages only, and not a penalty; and (ii) represent a reasonable and good faith attempt by Lobos and the Driver and Company to ascertain the minimum damages that would be suffered by Lobos in the event of the default or early  termination of this Agreement. The parties further acknowledge that Lobos from the onset of the Agreement will have invested significant time and money to assist the Company and Driver in paying for and performing the Services set forth in this Agreement. The parties further acknowledge that Lobos from the onset of the Agreement will have invested significant time and money to assist the Company and Driver in paying for and performing the Services set forth in this Agreement.</li>
					<p>If the Driver and Company fails to pay such Termination Fee, whether due to an Event of Default or early termination pursuant to Section 3 above, Lobos shall be entitled to all remedies conferred upon Lobos by law and by the terms of this Agreement and may exercise any and all rights and remedies available to a secured creditor under applicable law, including foreclosure of the Driver's Collateral and/or Collateral pursuant to Article 9 of the Utah Uniform Commercial Code.</p>
				</ol>
